# SLA and Performance Rules

Track every prescription from the second it enters the system.

Track:

- time before typing starts
- time spent typing
- time before PV1 starts
- time spent in PV1
- time before filling starts
- time spent filling
- time before final verification starts
- time spent in final verification
- time before shipping receives the order
- time shipping takes until shipped

Use detailed interval records, not only timestamp columns.

Required intervals:

- WAIT_BEFORE_TYPING
- TYPING_ACTIVE
- WAIT_BEFORE_PV1
- PV1_ACTIVE
- WAIT_BEFORE_FILL
- FILL_ACTIVE
- WAIT_BEFORE_FINAL_VERIFICATION
- FINAL_VERIFICATION_ACTIVE
- WAIT_BEFORE_SHIPPING
- SHIPPING_ACTIVE

Orders over SLA should show warning/yellow, breach/red, and then move or appear in an emergency bucket.

Cancellation must go through CancelOrder command and requires:

- disposition reason
- user stamp
- cancelled_from_status
- command_log
- order_event
- audit_log
- event_outbox

Track application-level activity only:

- login
- logout
- heartbeat
- order opened
- queue claimed
- command started
- command completed
- scan
- print
- idle started
- idle ended

Do not track screenshots, keystrokes, unrelated websites, or personal device activity.
